cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CC, cs.DL, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new self-index data structure based on the LZ77 compression format. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper mentions the self-index's ability to find patterns in text databases. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the efficiency of the self-index in terms of space and time complexity. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is another possibility as the paper mentions versioned document collections as an example of highly repetitive text collections. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also a possibility as the paper mentions sequence databases of genomes of related species as another example of highly repetitive text collections.
